      <h2>
        Our Gym
      </h2>
      <p>
        Soul MMA is one of Ireland’s original Mixed Martial Arts and Brazilian Jiu Jitsu clubs, founded in 2002. 
        It began as a training club affiliated to Soul MMA under John Kavanagh based in NUIG, extending from the NUIG Taekwon-Do club.
        Its founding members included first generation Irish MMA fighters such as Mark Leonard, Vinny Connelly, Tom Haddock and 
        Mark O’Toole. We moved to our first full-time premises in 2006 in the Parkmore Business Park where the club was run by 
        Mark Leonard. In February 2011 Mark stepped aside and John Kavanagh took over as head coach. In May 2011 we moved to our new 
        facility in the Carriganore in the new purpose built facility in Waterford.
      </p>
      <p>
        Our purpose-built gym is close to local transport and has plenty of parking. A clean, modern facility, 
        it features a large matted area, a weights area, and a competition size MMA cage. It has both male and female 
        changing rooms and a shop so you can purchase any equipment that you need. We accept new members all the time so 
        contact us to enquire about a free trial class.
      </p>
      <p>
        We have an array of amateur and professional fighters, no matter if your just starting out or already an experienced fighter we have something to offer.

      </p>
    </div>

