        World Class Coaches
      </h2>
      <p>
        We have acquired excellent coaches throughout the years and are now considered the "premier" place to be for up and coming fighters hoping to join
        fighting organisations. Our coaches hail from all over the world and bring an interntional pedigree - the likes of which has never been seen before.
      </p>
      <p>
        In 2004, champion UFC fighter Daniel Cormier began training at the club during fight camps which then led to him taking up a full-time 
        role as our lead wrestling coach. Similarly, just 3 months later, Firas Zahabi joined as our head BJJ coach after having moved to Ireland with his family.
        In 2014 we added the greatest Muay Thai fighter to have ever lived as our head striking coach. Suphachai "Saenchai" Saepong moved to Ireland after having had
        a pint of guness whilst over here. He fell in love with it and decided that he would move over here so he could drink it at any time.
      </p>
      <p>
        You will be safe in the very experienced hands of all of our coaches. Our coaches offer free one-to-one sessions to members of our gym. This is where they can 
        take a personal approach to your fighting and fitness development.
      </p>
